During a network partition between DC and Cloud, the following scenario led the discovery client to get "null" applications.
If the outage happened exactly at the time of unmarshalling discovery data, a "null" value is returned by the discovery unmarshaller. If the network connection failed at the time of connection or when the response is read - it wouldn't be a problem. That is why this problem was not affecting all the servers.
Below is the sample exception trace that indicates the problem
